mber of grotesque murders from almost forty years ago, they begin to unravel a dark and appalling family history. But the Vangers are a secretive clan, and Blomkvist and Salander are about to find out just how far they are prepared to go to protect themselves. Written by Music Box Films','A journalist is aided in his search for a woman who has been missing -- or dead -- for forty years by a young female hacker.','http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTc2Mjc0MDg3MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMjUzMDkxMw@@._V1_SX214_.jpg','2010-07-09',7.8),(893,'A Knight\'s Tale',2001,'http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0183790','tt0183790',NULL,5,'Inspired by \"The Canterbury Tales,\" as well as the story of Ulrich von Lichtenstein, this is the story of William, a young squire with a gift for jousting. After his master dies suddenly, the squire hits the road with his cohorts Roland and Wat. On the journey, they stumble across an unknown writer, Chaucer. William, lacking a proper pedigree, convinces Chaucer to forge genealogy documents that will pass him off as a knight. With his newly-minted history in hand, the young man sets out to prove himself a worthy knight at the country\'s jousting competition, and finds romance along the way. Written by Anonymous','After his master dies, a peasant squire, fueled by his desire for food and glory, creates a new identity for himself as a knight.','http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/M/MV5BMTE5OTE4OTE2Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwMDkzMTQ3._V1_SX214_.jpg','2001-05-11',6.8),(894,'The Bourne Ultimatum',2007,'http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0440963','tt0440963',NULL,5,'Bourne is once again brought out of hiding, this time inadvertently by London-based reporter Simon Ross who is trying to unveil Operation Blackbriar--an upgrade to Project Treadstone--in a series of newspaper columns. Bourne sets up a meeting with Ross and realizes instantly they\'re being scanned. Information from the reporter stirs a new set of memories, and Bourne must finally, ultimately, uncover his dark past whi